## Severity
Minor
## Dimension
dry
## Location
src/plugins/mod.rs:541-613, src/plugins/mod.rs:333-360
## Violation
Five distinct branches handle the four MCP-config sources (.mcp.json conventional, manifest Path, manifest Map, manifest Array Path, manifest Array Map). Each branch re-implements `serde_json::from_str::<HashMap<String, McpServerConfig>>(&content)` independently, and only some branches honour the `mcpServers` wrapper key. Quoted lines:

    let mcp_json = self.path.join(".mcp.json");
    if mcp_json.exists() {
        if let Ok(content) = fs::read_to_string(&mcp_json) {
            ...
            if let Ok(servers) = serde_json::from_str::<HashMap<String, McpServerConfig>>(&content) {
                self.mcp_configs.extend(servers);
            }
        }
    }
    ...
    McpServersSpec::Path(p) => {
        let resolved = self.path.join(p);
        if resolved.exists() {
            if let Ok(content) = fs::read_to_string(&resolved) {
                if let Ok(servers) = serde_json::from_str::<HashMap<String, McpServerConfig>>(&content) {
                    self.mcp_configs.extend(servers);
                }
            }
        }
    }

Drift between branches: the conventional path falls back to the bare map if `mcpServers` is missing, but McpServersSpec::Path does NOT — the user gets different behaviour depending on whether they reference the file via convention or via manifest. Same drift in McpServersSpec::Array::Path. Identical 4-line read-and-parse blocks repeat 5 times.
## Mandated refactor
Extract `fn load_mcp_file(path: &Path) -> Result<HashMap<String, McpServerConfig>, PluginError>` that handles BOTH the wrapper and the bare-map formats and reuse it from every branch. Reduce the resolve_mcp_servers function to ~25 lines and make the convention/manifest semantics indistinguishable.
